##########################
# How to execute a test ? 
#########################


To realize a test, the ss_rank_tx.py needs to be started in two terminals.
IMPORTANT:
	1 - TWO USRPS are needed, both with a WBX board.
	2 - Use antennas OR connect the USRP using the low loss cable( in this case connect the TX of the first USRP in the RX of the second USRP and the RX of the first USRP in the TX of the second.

1) Start the first ss_rank_tx.py for RECEPTION of packets:

	./ss_rank_tx.py --interferer --args addr=<USRP 1 IP> --log --mode {txonly, ss} --samp-rate <samp rate> --duration <test duration> --pkt-size <packet size> --platform <hp, mac, etc (for log only)> --iteration <test iteration (for log only> --sending-duration <single transmission time> --sensing-duration <single sensing time> &


2) Start the second ss_rank_tx.py for TRANSMISSION and CHANNEL DECISION:

	./ss_rank_tx.py --args addr=<USRP 2 IP> --log --mode {txonly, ss} --samp-rate <samp rate> --duration <test duration> --pkt-size <packet size> --platform <hp, mac, etc (for log only)> --iteration <test iteration (for log only> --sending-duration <single transmission time> --sensing-duration <single sensing time> &


3) Wait the test to finish



NOTES:
	1 - To repeat the same experiments realized in the paper "Open Environment for Radio Applications: Development and Experimentation" execute the do_test.bash script. Check the script to alter the USRP parameters

##########################
# How to plot results ? 
#########################
Execute:
 ./plot <platform>
or
 ./plot comparison


If needed, edit the ITERATIONS variable to set the platform-iterations executed. By default, the platforms are 'mac', 'hp' and 'p4', each with 20 iterations.

If you change the platforms, the ./plot comparison script will not work (feel free to edit the script)



